title: Independent candidate Iftikhar Ahmad Jadoun wins PK-44 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Iftikhar Ahmad Jadoun has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-44, Abbottabad-III by securing 34,867 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Sardar Aurangzaib who bagged 32,585 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 42.52 per cent.
